## 3. select()

✅ Excellent

Both styles were correctly used.

```r
select(train, ...)
```

and

```r
train |>
    select(...)
```

Also verified using

```r
identical()
```

which is a good debugging habit.

---

## 4. filter()

✅ Excellent

Single-condition filtering

```r
SalePrice >= 200000
```

and multiple conditions

```r
SalePrice >= 200000,
PoolArea > 0
```

were both correct.

Good understanding that commas inside `filter()` mean logical AND.

---

## 5. `%in%`

✅ Excellent

Correctly recognized that

```r
OverallQual %in% c(8,9,10)
```

is equivalent to

```r
OverallQual == 8 |
OverallQual == 9 |
OverallQual == 10
```

This will be very useful later for feature engineering.

---

## 6. mutate()

✅ Excellent

Created

```r
SalePrice_10k
```

correctly.

Also checked the result immediately.

Good habit.

---

## 7. if_else()

✅ Correct

```r
if_else(
    SalePrice >= 200000,
    "High",
    "Low"
)
```

Exactly as intended.

---

## 8. case_when()

✅ Correct

```r
case_when(
    SalePrice < 150000 ~ "Low",
    SalePrice < 250000 ~ "Middle",
    TRUE ~ "High"
)
```

Correct understanding that conditions are evaluated from top to bottom.

No need to explicitly write

```r
SalePrice >= 150000 &
```

because the previous condition has already excluded those rows.

---

