## 10. Missing Values

⚠ Small syntax mistake

Incorrect:

```r
mean(train$LotFrontage, NA=True)
```

Correct:

```r
mean(train$LotFrontage, na.rm = TRUE)
```

Important:

* `NA` is a missing value.
* `na.rm` means "remove missing values."

This argument appears frequently in R.

---

## 11. Pipe Workflow

✅ Excellent

The following workflow was written correctly.

```r
select()

↓

filter()

↓

mutate()

↓

head()
```

This is the basic data analysis pipeline used in almost every project.

---

## 12. Error Analysis

Excellent explanation.

```r
select(SalePrice, PoolArea)
```

removes

```r
OverallQual
```

Therefore

```r
filter(OverallQual >= 8)
```

cannot work afterward.

This shows good understanding of how data flows through a pipe.

